Ian 'anyuzer' Reid is just an attention deprived shithead and nothing more than just that. 
<br />

<br />
So what? Does it really matter to people what someone does with their life when they step away from their desk? Mr. Reid is going bonkers trying to get a reaction out of Furor. He is running out of material so he chose to dig deep and post about his real life, moving himself a step closer to being Furor's own internet stalker. 
<br />

<br />
It's kind of amusing since I'd just vented on Mrs. Juwel over this topic. I was saying how much it annoyed me to read it but I keep finding myself following link after link to this topic. 
<br />

<br />
There is not one person out there who has <span style="font-weight: bold">any</span> right to judge someone based on their online personality. Even if they make the choice to, I do not see the need to dedicate one front page after another to someone they <span style="font-style: italic">love to hate</span>. I'm sure it all boils down to jealousy. Maybe Furor was loud, vulgar and so much more but if you know your history he made a lot of things change for the better in EQ and he will continue to do that in WoW. It does not matter if he is an employee or just a customer, his voice matters and things he has voiced in the past have never gone unheard. 
<br />

<br />
I know there are people here who have had the chance to meet Alex aka Furor in real life as I have. <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" /> And I assure you, if he were anything like 'Furor' I'd have nothing to do with him. He is a brilliant, talented, kind and simply amazing person. I wouldn't know where to begin to describe him but I know that if anyone was best fit for the job, it would be him. 
<br />

