Furor acts like a jackass, much of the time, in good words and in bad, on his forum and on others about topics other than his discontent with EQ.  Pissing and moaning over Everquest is a pasttime to most players; flaming and spewing four letter words is a pasttime for Furor.  Do I really care that much?  No, not really.  But I do think that people have every right to judge him for mistreating others.  And maybe you don't believe he does, which just means that you and others have a differing view of his actions on public forums.  
<br />

<br />
If that isn't how he acts in real life, well, I'm not surprised.  Not many people could act that way in real life, without any internet cover, and actually live past the age of, oh, five.  But despite how he presents himself to the world, given how he acts when he is behind his internet avatar, its pretty clear there is a little flaming furor somewhere in that talented, kind persona.  And for little flaming furor's childishness and his rudeness and his harshness and his meanness people will judge him for it. And in my opinion, although I understand you may disagree, they are justified in doing so.  /shrug</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
