                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><span style="font-style: italic">How you act online is a reflection of you as a person.</span>
<br />

<br />
This is very true.  But I'll go a step further - how you act ALL THE TIME is a reflection of you as a person.  Character is evident in our every action.
<br />

<br />
Furor's okay.  I've only dealt with him a couple of times, but I'm used to dealing with Zaar, so same difference.
<br />

<br />
At any rate, I think hiring Furor was a Good Thing(tm). One of the things we've seen pretty much with every MMOG is an abysmal lack of high end content.  And I don't mean just uberguild content, I'm talking about people maxing out early, getting bored, and leaving the game.   The fact that guys like Furor, Tigole, and a few other high-end players I shall decline to name are getting hired to do high-end game design is a huge plus for those of us who like to hardcore our way up - and then find ourselves with nothing to do.  I think these guys will add depth to the games they work on and provide a more well-rounded gaming experience for all involved.  I am anxious to see the work they do.
<br />

