                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Me? I'm happy Furor joined up with Blizzard. I was happy way back when Tigole posted on the LoS site that he was going to work there too 'on a big project' (WoW).
<br />

<br />
Tigole...Furor...some other names that have shaped EQ, or our understanding of EQ high end stuff. I'm certainly not a fanboi of either of these two names, just that it <span style="font-style: italic">helps</span> the development of any game if you have people on your workforce/dev-team who have an extensive (and intensive) knowledge of gaming...in this case MMOs.
<br />

<br />
If I look at what some are calling 'the next big MMORPG' to come - Vanguard from Sigil Games - I see some well known people in the industry some of which were at the starting up of EQ when it was still Verant calling most of the shots, but not one person who we know/knew from EQ or UO. Maybe that will change.
<br />

<br />
IMO it's smart to hire people who have played these types of games, and I personaly couldn't care how crude they might seem on some messageboards or in game.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-weight: bold">V i s i o n a r y . F u n x i</span>.Legendary.tribunal
