                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">His online persona has nothing at all to do with his ability to work. Blizzard doesn't need to take any of that into consideration. They need to take his talent and experience into consideration, and obviously that is what they did. I personally do not feel that Blizzard or Furor needs to make a public speech to inform the gamers of who their employee's are. Blizzard's job is to build a good game for their customers to enjoy. <span style="font-weight: bold">If</span> Furor works there, his job is to do his best at what he was hired to do, which I think, no matter what the situation is, he is capable of doing. Again, that is just <span style="font-style: italic">my</span> personal opinion and I don't expect the world to agree with me.
<br />

<br />
If people want to judge people based on message forum personalities thats fine. I'm saying that his forum personality doesn't have a damn thing to do with his ability to work. You can't justify saying someone would be a bad employee because they are an asshole on message forums. Even if he is an asshole in real life, it still has nothing to do with how well he can do his job.
<br />

<br />
You don't need to agree with me, and I don't need to agree with you. I'm just saying I know for a fact he is talented and not a bad person. It is fine that people do not think that. I was basically trying to inform people who look past their computer screen that he is more than capable of helping to make an already great game even better. That is what matters the most, atleast to me. <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" />
