                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Your online persona shows what you're like in real life?  My ass.  People act much differently outside of games and messages boards online due to one reason, they are all held accountable for their actions to some extent and people will know who they are.
<br />

<br />
On the internet you are for the most part, Anonymous.  Do any of you know where i live, my name, my phone number, anything?  Hell can you pinpoint which time zone I'm in?  Unless I've told you probably not.  When people can be anonymous they act a hell of a lot different than when they are talking to someone in person.  I can scream at you, curse at you, and guess what?  You can't do a damn thing about it cause you don't even know who I am!!!!(yes I am well aware an admin can see my IP and eventually trace back my name etc =P)
<br />

<br />
You really think the way Furor posts on message boards is how he talks to people in real life?  There are a LOT of people who act just like him on message boards that play EQ, I'm willing to bet you have a few in your guild since there are some in every guild.  He was just the "loudest" voice of the different people screaming at SoE or at other people in general.
<br />

<br />
He works for Blizzard now, and will represent their company when he posts.  He no longer is "anonymous" on message boards and I'm willing to bet he'll act more like he does in real life because of it.  Since his job is sitting right there with him.
<br />

<br />
On the offside, when people start bitching about one thing or another in WoW especially when it deals with quests, who will be the person they blame?  He'll just be on the other side of the fence this time.
<br />

<br />

<br />
